1 in t he Oklahoma Medical Marijuana and Patient Protection Act, the
2 physician shall notify the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority and
3 the license shall be immediately voided without right to an
4 individual proceeding.
5 F. The Authority shall create and maintain a registry of
6 recommending physicians. Beginning January 1, 2026, to be eligible
7 to provide a medical marijuana recommendation to a licensed patient,
8 a physician shall be registered with the Authority.
9 G. To be registered with the Authority, a physician shall
10 comply with the medical education and continuing medical education
11 requirements described in this section and shall meet all other
12 requirements established by law or rule for the recommending
13 physician’s respective licensure board. The medical education
14 related to medical marijuana shall be completed prior to the
15 physician being listed on the registry and shall be completed
16 annually to remain on the registry.
17 H. The Executive Director of the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana
18 Authority shall promulgate rules to establish initial medical
19 education and continuing medical education requirements for
20 recommending physicians. The State Board of Medical Licensure and
21 Supervision, the State Board of Osteopathic Examiners, and the Board
22 of Podiatric Medical Examiners may consult with the Executive
23 Director of the Authority to develop or identify a list of approved
24 medical education courses for recommending physicians.
